{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I grew up on a steady diet of science fiction."},{"time":5000,"text":"In high school, I took a bus to school"},{"time":8000,"text":"an hour each way every day."},{"time":10000,"text":"And I was always absorbed in a book,"},{"time":12000,"text":"science fiction book,"},{"time":14000,"text":"which took my mind to other worlds,"},{"time":17000,"text":"and satisfied, in a narrative form,"},{"time":21000,"text":"this insatiable sense of curiosity that I had."}]},{"cues":[{"time":26000,"text":"And you know, that curiosity also manifested itself"},{"time":29000,"text":"in the fact that whenever I wasn't in school"},{"time":32000,"text":"I was out in the woods,"},{"time":34000,"text":"hiking and taking \"samples\" --"},{"time":38000,"text":"frogs and snakes and bugs and pond water --"},{"time":40000,"text":"and bringing it back, looking at it under the microscope."},{"time":43000,"text":"You know, I was a real science geek."},{"time":45000,"text":"But it was all about trying to understand the world,"},{"time":48000,"text":"understand the limits of possibility."}]},{"cues":[{"time":52000,"text":"And my love of science fiction"},{"time":56000,"text":"actually seemed mirrored in the world around me,"},{"time":59000,"text":"because what was happening, this was in the late '60s,"},{"time":61000,"text":"we were going to the moon,"},{"time":64000,"text":"we were exploring the deep oceans."},{"time":66000,"text":"Jacques Cousteau was coming into our living rooms"},{"time":69000,"text":"with his amazing specials that showed us"},{"time":72000,"text":"animals and places and a wondrous world"},{"time":74000,"text":"that we could never really have previously imagined."},{"time":77000,"text":"So, that seemed to resonate"},{"time":79000,"text":"with the whole science fiction part of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":82000,"text":"And I was an artist."},{"time":84000,"text":"I could draw. I could paint."},{"time":86000,"text":"And I found that because there weren't video games"},{"time":89000,"text":"and this saturation of CG movies and all of this"},{"time":93000,"text":"imagery in the media landscape,"},{"time":96000,"text":"I had to create these images in my head."},{"time":98000,"text":"You know, we all did, as kids having to"},{"time":100000,"text":"read a book, and through the author's description,"},{"time":103000,"text":"put something on the movie screen in our heads."},{"time":107000,"text":"And so, my response to this was to paint, to draw"},{"time":110000,"text":"alien creatures, alien worlds,"},{"time":112000,"text":"robots, spaceships, all that stuff."},{"time":114000,"text":"I was endlessly getting busted in math class"},{"time":117000,"text":"doodling behind the textbook."},{"time":120000,"text":"That was -- the creativity"},{"time":123000,"text":"had to find its outlet somehow."}]},{"cues":[{"time":127000,"text":"And an interesting thing happened: The Jacques Cousteau shows"},{"time":130000,"text":"actually got me very excited about the fact that there was"},{"time":133000,"text":"an alien world right here on Earth."},{"time":135000,"text":"I might not really go to an alien world"},{"time":138000,"text":"on a spaceship someday --"},{"time":140000,"text":"that seemed pretty darn unlikely."},{"time":143000,"text":"But that was a world I could really go to,"},{"time":145000,"text":"right here on Earth, that was as rich and exotic"},{"time":147000,"text":"as anything that I had imagined"},{"time":150000,"text":"from reading these books."}]},{"cues":[{"time":152000,"text":"So, I decided I was going to become a scuba diver"},{"time":154000,"text":"at the age of 15."},{"time":156000,"text":"And the only problem with that was that I lived"},{"time":158000,"text":"in a little village in Canada,"},{"time":160000,"text":"600 miles from the nearest ocean."},{"time":163000,"text":"But I didn't let that daunt me."},{"time":165000,"text":"I pestered my father until he finally found"},{"time":168000,"text":"a scuba class in Buffalo, New York,"},{"time":170000,"text":"right across the border from where we live."},{"time":172000,"text":"And I actually got certified"},{"time":175000,"text":"in a pool at a YMCA in the dead of winter"},{"time":177000,"text":"in Buffalo, New York."},{"time":179000,"text":"And I didn't see the ocean, a real ocean,"},{"time":182000,"text":"for another two years,"},{"time":184000,"text":"until we moved to California."}]},{"cues":[{"time":186000,"text":"Since then, in the intervening"},{"time":189000,"text":"40 years,"},{"time":191000,"text":"I've spent about 3,000 hours underwater,"},{"time":195000,"text":"and 500 hours of that was in submersibles."},{"time":198000,"text":"And I've learned that that deep-ocean environment,"},{"time":201000,"text":"and even the shallow oceans,"},{"time":203000,"text":"are so rich with amazing life"},{"time":207000,"text":"that really is beyond our imagination."},{"time":210000,"text":"Nature's imagination is so boundless"},{"time":214000,"text":"compared to our own"},{"time":216000,"text":"meager human imagination."},{"time":218000,"text":"I still, to this day, stand in absolute awe"},{"time":220000,"text":"of what I see when I make these dives."},{"time":223000,"text":"And my love affair with the ocean is ongoing,"},{"time":226000,"text":"and just as strong as it ever was."}]},{"cues":[{"time":228000,"text":"But when I chose a career as an adult,"},{"time":231000,"text":"it was filmmaking."},{"time":234000,"text":"And that seemed to be the best way to reconcile"},{"time":237000,"text":"this urge I had to tell stories"},{"time":239000,"text":"with my urges to create images."},{"time":243000,"text":"And I was, as a kid, constantly drawing comic books, and so on."},{"time":246000,"text":"So, filmmaking was the way to put pictures and stories"},{"time":248000,"text":"together, and that made sense."},{"time":250000,"text":"And of course the stories that I chose to tell"},{"time":253000,"text":"were science fiction stories: \"Terminator,\" \"Aliens\""},{"time":255000,"text":"and \"The Abyss.\""},{"time":257000,"text":"And with \"The Abyss,\" I was putting together my love"},{"time":260000,"text":"of underwater and diving with filmmaking."},{"time":262000,"text":"So, you know, merging the two passions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":265000,"text":"Something interesting came out of \"The Abyss,\""},{"time":269000,"text":"which was that to solve a specific narrative"},{"time":272000,"text":"problem on that film,"},{"time":275000,"text":"which was to create this kind of liquid water creature,"},{"time":279000,"text":"we actually embraced computer generated animation, CG."},{"time":285000,"text":"And this resulted in the first soft-surface"},{"time":290000,"text":"character, CG animation"},{"time":293000,"text":"that was ever in a movie."},{"time":295000,"text":"And even though the film didn't make any money --"},{"time":297000,"text":"barely broke even, I should say --"},{"time":300000,"text":"I witnessed something amazing, which is that the audience,"},{"time":302000,"text":"the global audience, was mesmerized"},{"time":304000,"text":"by this apparent magic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":306000,"text":"You know, it's Arthur Clarke's law"},{"time":308000,"text":"that any sufficiently advanced technology is indistinguishable from magic."},{"time":312000,"text":"They were seeing something magical."},{"time":315000,"text":"And so that got me very excited."},{"time":318000,"text":"And I thought, \"Wow, this is something that needs to be embraced"},{"time":320000,"text":"into the cinematic art.\""},{"time":322000,"text":"So, with \"Terminator 2,\" which was my next film,"},{"time":324000,"text":"we took that much farther."},{"time":326000,"text":"Working with ILM, we created the liquid metal dude"},{"time":329000,"text":"in that film. The success hung in the balance"},{"time":331000,"text":"on whether that effect would work."},{"time":333000,"text":"And it did, and we created magic again,"},{"time":335000,"text":"and we had the same result with an audience --"},{"time":337000,"text":"although we did make a little more money on that one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":339000,"text":"So, drawing a line through those two dots"},{"time":344000,"text":"of experience"},{"time":347000,"text":"came to, \"This is going to be a whole new world,\""},{"time":349000,"text":"this was a whole new world of creativity"},{"time":351000,"text":"for film artists."},{"time":354000,"text":"So, I started a company with Stan Winston,"},{"time":356000,"text":"my good friend Stan Winston,"},{"time":358000,"text":"who is the premier make-up and creature designer"},{"time":362000,"text":"at that time, and it was called Digital Domain."},{"time":365000,"text":"And the concept of the company was"},{"time":367000,"text":"that we would leapfrog past"},{"time":370000,"text":"the analog processes of optical printers and so on,"},{"time":373000,"text":"and we would go right to digital production."},{"time":375000,"text":"And we actually did that and it gave us a competitive advantage for a while."}]},{"cues":[{"time":379000,"text":"But we found ourselves lagging in the mid '90s"},{"time":382000,"text":"in the creature and character design stuff"},{"time":385000,"text":"that we had actually founded the company to do."},{"time":388000,"text":"So, I wrote this piece called \"Avatar,\""},{"time":390000,"text":"which was meant to absolutely push the envelope"},{"time":394000,"text":"of visual effects,"},{"time":396000,"text":"of CG effects, beyond,"},{"time":398000,"text":"with realistic human emotive characters"},{"time":402000,"text":"generated in CG,"},{"time":404000,"text":"and the main characters would all be in CG,"},{"time":406000,"text":"and the world would be in CG."},{"time":408000,"text":"And the envelope pushed back,"},{"time":410000,"text":"and I was told by the folks at my company"},{"time":415000,"text":"that we weren't going to be able to do this for a while."}]},{"cues":[{"time":417000,"text":"So, I shelved it, and I made this other movie about a big ship that sinks."},{"time":421000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":424000,"text":"You know, I went and pitched it to the studio as \"'Romeo and Juliet' on a ship:"},{"time":427000,"text":"\"It's going to be this epic romance,"},{"time":429000,"text":"passionate film.\""},{"time":431000,"text":"Secretly, what I wanted to do was"},{"time":433000,"text":"I wanted to dive to the real wreck of \"Titanic.\""},{"time":436000,"text":"And that's why I made the movie."},{"time":438000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":442000,"text":"And that's the truth. Now, the studio didn't know that."},{"time":444000,"text":"But I convinced them. I said,"},{"time":446000,"text":"\"We're going to dive to the wreck. We're going to film it for real."},{"time":448000,"text":"We'll be using it in the opening of the film."},{"time":451000,"text":"It will be really important. It will be a great marketing hook.\""},{"time":453000,"text":"And I talked them into funding an expedition."},{"time":455000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":457000,"text":"Sounds crazy. But this goes back to that theme"},{"time":459000,"text":"about your imagination creating a reality."},{"time":462000,"text":"Because we actually created a reality where six months later,"},{"time":464000,"text":"I find myself in a Russian submersible"},{"time":466000,"text":"two and a half miles down in the north Atlantic,"},{"time":469000,"text":"looking at the real Titanic through a view port."},{"time":471000,"text":"Not a movie, not HD -- for real."},{"time":474000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":477000,"text":"Now, that blew my mind."},{"time":479000,"text":"And it took a lot of preparation, we had to build cameras"},{"time":481000,"text":"and lights and all kinds of things."},{"time":483000,"text":"But, it struck me how much"},{"time":485000,"text":"this dive, these deep dives,"},{"time":487000,"text":"was like a space mission."},{"time":489000,"text":"You know, where it was highly technical,"},{"time":491000,"text":"and it required enormous planning."},{"time":493000,"text":"You get in this capsule, you go down to this dark"},{"time":495000,"text":"hostile environment"},{"time":498000,"text":"where there is no hope of rescue"},{"time":500000,"text":"if you can't get back by yourself."},{"time":502000,"text":"And I thought like, \"Wow. I'm like,"},{"time":504000,"text":"living in a science fiction movie."},{"time":506000,"text":"This is really cool.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":508000,"text":"And so, I really got bitten by the bug of deep-ocean exploration."},{"time":511000,"text":"Of course, the curiosity, the science component of it --"},{"time":514000,"text":"it was everything. It was adventure,"},{"time":516000,"text":"it was curiosity, it was imagination."},{"time":518000,"text":"And it was an experience that"},{"time":521000,"text":"Hollywood couldn't give me."},{"time":523000,"text":"Because, you know, I could imagine a creature and we could"},{"time":525000,"text":"create a visual effect for it. But I couldn't imagine what I was seeing"},{"time":527000,"text":"out that window."},{"time":529000,"text":"As we did some of our subsequent expeditions,"},{"time":532000,"text":"I was seeing creatures at hydrothermal vents"},{"time":534000,"text":"and sometimes things that I had never seen before,"},{"time":538000,"text":"sometimes things that no one had seen before,"},{"time":540000,"text":"that actually were not described by science"},{"time":542000,"text":"at the time that we saw them and imaged them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":545000,"text":"So, I was completely smitten by this,"},{"time":548000,"text":"and had to do more."},{"time":550000,"text":"And so, I actually made a kind of curious decision."},{"time":552000,"text":"After the success of \"Titanic,\""},{"time":554000,"text":"I said, \"OK, I'm going to park my day job"},{"time":557000,"text":"as a Hollywood movie maker,"},{"time":559000,"text":"and I'm going to go be a full-time explorer for a while.\""},{"time":563000,"text":"And so, we started planning these"},{"time":565000,"text":"expeditions."},{"time":567000,"text":"And we wound up going to the Bismark,"},{"time":569000,"text":"and exploring it with robotic vehicles."},{"time":573000,"text":"We went back to the Titanic wreck."},{"time":575000,"text":"We took little bots that we had created"},{"time":577000,"text":"that spooled a fiber optic."},{"time":579000,"text":"And the idea was to go in and do an interior"},{"time":581000,"text":"survey of that ship, which had never been done."},{"time":585000,"text":"Nobody had ever looked inside the wreck. They didn't have the means to do it,"},{"time":587000,"text":"so we created technology to do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":590000,"text":"So, you know, here I am now, on the deck"},{"time":592000,"text":"of Titanic, sitting in a submersible,"},{"time":595000,"text":"and looking out at planks that look much like this,"},{"time":598000,"text":"where I knew that the band had played."},{"time":601000,"text":"And I'm flying a little robotic vehicle"},{"time":603000,"text":"through the corridor of the ship."},{"time":606000,"text":"When I say, \"I'm operating it,\""},{"time":609000,"text":"but my mind is in the vehicle."},{"time":612000,"text":"I felt like I was physically present"},{"time":614000,"text":"inside the shipwreck of Titanic."},{"time":616000,"text":"And it was the most surreal kind"},{"time":618000,"text":"of deja vu experience I've ever had,"},{"time":620000,"text":"because I would know before I turned a corner"},{"time":624000,"text":"what was going to be there before the lights"},{"time":626000,"text":"of the vehicle actually revealed it,"},{"time":628000,"text":"because I had walked the set for months"},{"time":630000,"text":"when we were making the movie."},{"time":633000,"text":"And the set was based as an exact replica"},{"time":635000,"text":"on the blueprints of the ship."}]},{"cues":[{"time":637000,"text":"So, it was this absolutely remarkable experience."},{"time":640000,"text":"And it really made me realize that"},{"time":642000,"text":"the telepresence experience --"},{"time":644000,"text":"that you actually can have these robotic avatars,"},{"time":646000,"text":"then your consciousness is injected into the vehicle,"},{"time":651000,"text":"into this other form of existence."},{"time":653000,"text":"It was really, really quite profound."},{"time":655000,"text":"And it may be a little bit of a glimpse as to what might be happening"},{"time":658000,"text":"some decades out"},{"time":660000,"text":"as we start to have cyborg bodies"},{"time":663000,"text":"for exploration or for other means"},{"time":665000,"text":"in many sort of"},{"time":667000,"text":"post-human futures"},{"time":669000,"text":"that I can imagine,"},{"time":671000,"text":"as a science fiction fan."}]},{"cues":[{"time":673000,"text":"So, having done these expeditions,"},{"time":678000,"text":"and really beginning to appreciate what was down there,"},{"time":682000,"text":"such as at the deep ocean vents"},{"time":685000,"text":"where we had these amazing, amazing animals --"},{"time":688000,"text":"they're basically aliens right here on Earth."},{"time":690000,"text":"They live in an environment of chemosynthesis."},{"time":693000,"text":"They don't survive on sunlight-based"},{"time":695000,"text":"system the way we do."},{"time":697000,"text":"And so, you're seeing animals that are living next to"},{"time":699000,"text":"a 500-degree-Centigrade"},{"time":701000,"text":"water plumes."},{"time":703000,"text":"You think they can't possibly exist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":705000,"text":"At the same time"},{"time":707000,"text":"I was getting very interested in space science as well --"},{"time":710000,"text":"again, it's the science fiction influence, as a kid."},{"time":713000,"text":"And I wound up getting involved with"},{"time":715000,"text":"the space community,"},{"time":717000,"text":"really involved with NASA,"},{"time":719000,"text":"sitting on the NASA advisory board,"},{"time":722000,"text":"planning actual space missions,"},{"time":724000,"text":"going to Russia, going through the pre-cosmonaut"},{"time":726000,"text":"biomedical protocols,"},{"time":728000,"text":"and all these sorts of things,"},{"time":730000,"text":"to actually go and fly to the international space station"},{"time":732000,"text":"with our 3D camera systems."},{"time":734000,"text":"And this was fascinating."},{"time":736000,"text":"But what I wound up doing was bringing space scientists"},{"time":738000,"text":"with us into the deep."},{"time":741000,"text":"And taking them down so that they had access --"},{"time":744000,"text":"astrobiologists, planetary scientists,"},{"time":747000,"text":"people who were interested in these extreme environments --"},{"time":750000,"text":"taking them down to the vents, and letting them see,"},{"time":753000,"text":"and take samples and test instruments, and so on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":755000,"text":"So, here we were making documentary films,"},{"time":757000,"text":"but actually doing science,"},{"time":759000,"text":"and actually doing space science."},{"time":761000,"text":"I'd completely closed the loop"},{"time":763000,"text":"between being the science fiction fan,"},{"time":765000,"text":"you know, as a kid,"},{"time":767000,"text":"and doing this stuff for real."},{"time":769000,"text":"And you know, along the way in this journey"},{"time":772000,"text":"of discovery,"},{"time":774000,"text":"I learned a lot."},{"time":776000,"text":"I learned a lot about science. But I also learned a lot"},{"time":778000,"text":"about leadership."},{"time":781000,"text":"Now you think director has got to be a leader,"},{"time":783000,"text":"leader of, captain of the ship, and all that sort of thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":785000,"text":"I didn't really learn about leadership"},{"time":787000,"text":"until I did these expeditions."},{"time":790000,"text":"Because I had to, at a certain point, say,"},{"time":793000,"text":"\"What am I doing out here?"},{"time":795000,"text":"Why am I doing this? What do I get out of it?\""},{"time":798000,"text":"We don't make money at these damn shows."},{"time":801000,"text":"We barely break even. There is no fame in it."},{"time":803000,"text":"People sort of think I went away"},{"time":805000,"text":"between \"Titanic\" and \"Avatar\" and was buffing my nails"},{"time":807000,"text":"someplace, sitting at the beach."},{"time":809000,"text":"Made all these films, made all these documentary films"},{"time":812000,"text":"for a very limited audience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":814000,"text":"No fame, no glory, no money. What are you doing?"},{"time":817000,"text":"You're doing it for the task itself,"},{"time":819000,"text":"for the challenge --"},{"time":821000,"text":"and the ocean is the most challenging environment there is --"},{"time":824000,"text":"for the thrill of discovery,"},{"time":827000,"text":"and for that strange bond that happens"},{"time":830000,"text":"when a small group of people form a tightly knit team."},{"time":833000,"text":"Because we would do these things with 10, 12 people,"},{"time":836000,"text":"working for years at a time,"},{"time":838000,"text":"sometimes at sea for two, three months at a time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":842000,"text":"And in that bond, you realize"},{"time":845000,"text":"that the most important thing"},{"time":847000,"text":"is the respect that you have for them"},{"time":849000,"text":"and that they have for you, that you've done a task"},{"time":852000,"text":"that you can't explain to someone else."},{"time":854000,"text":"When you come back to the shore and you say,"},{"time":856000,"text":"\"We had to do this, and the fiber optic, and the attentuation,"},{"time":858000,"text":"and the this and the that,"},{"time":860000,"text":"all the technology of it, and the difficulty,"},{"time":862000,"text":"the human-performance aspects of working at sea,\""},{"time":865000,"text":"you can't explain it to people. It's that thing that"},{"time":867000,"text":"maybe cops have, or people in combat that have gone through something together"},{"time":871000,"text":"and they know they can never explain it."},{"time":873000,"text":"Creates a bond, creates a bond of respect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":875000,"text":"So, when I came back to make my next movie,"},{"time":877000,"text":"which was \"Avatar,\""},{"time":880000,"text":"I tried to apply that same principle of leadership,"},{"time":883000,"text":"which is that you respect your team,"},{"time":885000,"text":"and you earn their respect in return."},{"time":887000,"text":"And it really changed the dynamic."},{"time":889000,"text":"So, here I was again with a small team,"},{"time":892000,"text":"in uncharted territory,"},{"time":894000,"text":"doing \"Avatar,\" coming up with new technology"},{"time":896000,"text":"that didn't exist before."},{"time":898000,"text":"Tremendously exciting."},{"time":900000,"text":"Tremendously challenging."},{"time":902000,"text":"And we became a family, over a four-and-half year period."},{"time":904000,"text":"And it completely changed how I do movies."},{"time":907000,"text":"So, people have commented on how, \"Well, you know,"},{"time":909000,"text":"you brought back the ocean organisms"},{"time":912000,"text":"and put them on the planet of Pandora.\""},{"time":914000,"text":"To me, it was more of a fundamental way of doing business,"},{"time":916000,"text":"the process itself, that changed as a result of that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":920000,"text":"So, what can we synthesize out of all this?"},{"time":922000,"text":"You know, what are the lessons learned?"},{"time":925000,"text":"Well, I think number one is"},{"time":927000,"text":"curiosity."},{"time":929000,"text":"It's the most powerful thing you own."},{"time":932000,"text":"Imagination is a force"},{"time":935000,"text":"that can actually manifest a reality."},{"time":939000,"text":"And the respect of your team"},{"time":943000,"text":"is more important than all the"},{"time":945000,"text":"laurels in the world."},{"time":948000,"text":"I have young filmmakers"},{"time":950000,"text":"come up to me and say, \"Give me some advice for doing this.\""},{"time":954000,"text":"And I say, \"Don't put limitations on yourself."},{"time":958000,"text":"Other people will do that for you -- don't do it to yourself,"},{"time":960000,"text":"don't bet against yourself,"},{"time":962000,"text":"and take risks.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":964000,"text":"NASA has this phrase that they like:"},{"time":967000,"text":"\"Failure is not an option.\""},{"time":969000,"text":"But failure has to be an option"},{"time":972000,"text":"in art and in exploration, because it's a leap of faith."},{"time":975000,"text":"And no important endeavor"},{"time":977000,"text":"that required innovation"},{"time":979000,"text":"was done without risk."},{"time":981000,"text":"You have to be willing to take those risks."},{"time":984000,"text":"So, that's the thought I would leave you with,"},{"time":986000,"text":"is that in whatever you're doing,"},{"time":989000,"text":"failure is an option,"},{"time":992000,"text":"but fear is not. Thank you."},{"time":995000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}